article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- — Amar'e Marshall had 26 points in Albany's 91-67 victory against New Hampshire on Thursday night. Marshall also contributed 14 rebounds for the Great Danes (13-16, 5-9 America East Conference). Aaron Reddish added 20 points while going 7 of 10 from the floor, including 2 for 4 from 3-point range, and 4 for 4 from the line, and he also had five rebounds. Sebastian Thomas had 19 points and shot 8 for 17, including 1 for 7 from beyond the arc. The Wildcats (15-12, 7-7) were led by Trey Woodyard, who recorded 21 points and six rebounds. Jaxson Baker added 13 points and seven rebounds for New Hampshire. In addition, Christian Moore finished with 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
